        "subtopic": "Frequently Asked Questions",
        "content": "Q1. How many wildlife sanctuaries are there in India?\n• There are a total of 573 wildlife sanctuaries in India (as of Nov 2023).\n\nQ2. What percentage of India’s land area is covered by wildlife sanctuaries?\n• Around 3.76% of the nation’s geographical area.\n\nQ3. How many famous sanctuaries are there in India?\n• Out of 573 sanctuaries, only 24 are considered very famous.\n\nQ4. Which is the largest wildlife sanctuary in India?\n• The Rann of Kutch Desert Wildlife Sanctuary in Gujarat (approx. 7,500 km²).\n\nQ5. Which is the smallest wildlife sanctuary in India?\n• Bor Tiger Reserve’s Rani Jhansi Marine National Park is among the smallest, but officially the smallest sanctuary is the South Button Island National Park in Andaman & Nicobar (only 0.03 km²).\n\nQ6. Which is the first wildlife sanctuary of India?\n• Vedanthangal Bird Sanctuary in Tamil Nadu, established in 1796.\n\nQ7. Which state has the maximum number of wildlife sanctuaries?\n• Maharashtra has the highest number of wildlife sanctuaries.\n\nQ8. What is the difference between a National Park and a Wildlife Sanctuary?\n• National Parks are highly protected areas with no human activity allowed, whereas Wildlife Sanctuaries allow regulated human activities like grazing and tourism.\n\nQ9. How many biodiversity hotspots are there in India?\n• There are 3 biodiversity hotspots in India: Himalaya, Indo-Burma, and Indo-Malayan (Nicobar Islands).\n\nQ10. Which is the most famous bird sanctuary in India?\n• Bharatpur Bird Sanctuary (Keoladeo Ghana National Park) in Rajasthan."
